Juvenile Snowshoe Hares in Bonanza Creek Experimental Forest: Exploratory Report

Catherine Takata

20 Novemeber 2020

1. Introduction

In this exploratory report, based on the findings of “Snowshoe hare physical data in Bonanza Creek Experimental Forest: 1999-Present,” we identified differences and trends among observations on the Snowshoe hare of Bonanza Creek, Alaska, United States (Kielland et al. (2017). Female and male juvenile hare weights were compared and the relationship between weight and hind foot legnth was explored. Through data visualization, a series of test sampling, summary statistics, and regression analysis, this report provides an overview of a quanatative analysis of this keystone species.
